Use persistent data containers for effect IDS.  Setting custom model data makes it harder on the resource pack devs.
To get the character for the action bar:
  - If there is no effect in the slot, use "\ue901"
  - If there is an effect, use:
    ```
    int status = 0;
    if (effect.getAugmented()) status += 2;
    if (CooldownManager.isEffectActive(playerUUID, toInt())) status += 1;

    char emoji = (char) Integer.parseInt("E" + status + String.format("%02d", effect.getId()), 16);
    char = "E{status}{String.format("%02d", effect.getId())}"
    ```

Player Schedulers!  They cancel automatically if the player goes offline.
    player.getScheduler().runDelayed(plugin, task -> { if (maxHealthAttribute != null) maxHealthAttribute.setBaseValue(20); }, null, 1200);